---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Platform overview"
  description="Praxnote is one platform with three layers: documentation, workflow, and the platform underneath. Four roles share all of it."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="The platform"
    title="One workspace. <em>Three layers.</em> Four roles."
    lede="Praxnote isn't a documentation tool with a billing add-on, or a billing tool with a documentation add-on. It's three layers built together, for the four roles that actually run a behavioral-health practice."
  >
    <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book a demo</a>
    <a href="/security" class="btn btn-secondary">Security overview</a>
  </PageHeader>

  <section class="prose">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p>
        At the top is the <strong>clinical record</strong>. Fourteen editable AI skills draft
        session notes in five formats, treatment plans in five formats, referral and
        discharge letters, case conceptualizations, and assessment-results letters. Every
        prompt is a plain-text file. Practices customize the ones they want to. Clinicians edit and
        sign. The version of the skill in effect is captured with every draft.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the middle are the <strong>surfaces a practice runs on</strong>. The supervision
        queue with keyboard navigation. The calendar with availability blocks, self-scheduling,
        and waitlist routing. Billing with per-therapist rates, payment links, and Stripe
        autopay. The client portal with one-click sign-in links, secure messaging, document upload,
        and multilingual access. None of these are bolt-ons. They share one audit log, one
        security model, and one set of permissions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Underneath is the <strong>substrate</strong>. Encryption at rest and in transit. An
        activity log on every read and write. The right-to-erasure workflow that satisfies
        GDPR and PIPEDA without breaking HIPAA's six-year retention. A multilingual portal
        with a live translation system. The PIN-locked offline vault for clinicians whose
        practice doesn't always have wifi. These layers don't have surfaces of their own.
        They're the things the surfaces depend on.
      </p>
      <p>
        Four first-class roles share all of it: therapist, supervisor, practice administrator,
        and client. Each has its own permissions and its own navigation. A dual-role
        therapist-admin (the way most group-practice owners actually work) gets two themes
        and one identity, audit-logged accordingly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="diagram">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="stack" aria-labelledby="stack-caption">
        <div class="layer layer--top">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">01</span>
            <h3>Documentation</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>14 editable AI skills · session notes (SOAP · DAP · BIRP · narrative · custom) · treatment plans (PBT/EEMM · standard · CBT · DBT · simple) · diagnoses · case conceptualization · referral, discharge, and leave-of-absence letters · the assessments suite</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="layer layer--mid">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">02</span>
            <h3>Workflow</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>supervision queue · scheduling and waitlist · per-therapist billing with Stripe autopay · client portal with one-click sign-in · email and SMS templates · session-type and CPT-rate management</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="layer layer--bottom">
          <div class="layer-rail">
            <span class="layer-num">03</span>
            <h3>Platform</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="layer-body">
            <p>encryption at rest and in transit · activity log on every read and write · GDPR and PIPEDA right-to-erasure · multilingual portal with live translation · PIN-locked offline vault · audit-ready exports</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <figcaption id="stack-caption">Three layers, one platform. Same audit log, same encryption, same role model.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <aside class="roles-rail">
        <span class="rail-label">Four roles share all of it</span>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/solutions/solo-clinicians">Therapist</a></li>
          <li><a href="/solutions/supervisors">Supervisor</a></li>
          <li><a href="/solutions/practice-admins">Practice admin</a></li>
          <li><a href="/features/client-portal">Client</a></li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Long-form narrative */
  .prose { padding: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4.5rem) 0 clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); }
  .prose p {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.4vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--stone-900); font-weight: 600; }

  /* Layered diagram */
  .diagram { padding: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem) 0 clamp(4rem, 7vw, 6rem); }
  .stack {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .layer {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.85rem clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .layer:last-of-type { border-bottom: 0; }
  .layer--top { background: var(--surface-card); }
  .layer--mid { background: var(--paper-warm); }
  .layer--bottom { background: var(--surface-ink); color: var(--paper-warm); border-bottom: 0; }
  .layer-rail { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .layer-num {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--brand-teal);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-num { color: var(--brand-teal-soft); }
  .layer-rail h3 {
    font-size: 1.55rem;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--stone-900);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 30;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-rail h3 { color: var(--paper); }
  .layer-body p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .layer--bottom .layer-body p { color: rgba(250, 247, 242, 0.72); }

  .stack figcaption {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--paper);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--stone-500);
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .layer { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.85rem; padding: 1.5rem; }
    .layer-rail { flex-direction: row; align-items: baseline; gap: 0.85rem; }
  }

  /* Roles rail (separate, after the stack) */
  .roles-rail {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.75rem);
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  .rail-label {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--stone-700);
    font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 30;
  }
  .roles-rail ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .roles-rail li { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--stone-800); }
  .roles-rail a {
    color: var(--stone-800);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--hairline-strong);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
  }
  .roles-rail a:hover { color: var(--brand-teal-dark); border-bottom-color: var(--brand-teal); }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .roles-rail { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
